WHEREAS, a distinguished alumna of Southern University School of Nursing,
Renita Williams Thomas earned a Bachelor of Science in Nursing in 1997 and a Master of
Science in Nursing in 2012, exemplifying the university's enduring legacy of producing
leaders grounded in excellence, compassion, and service; and
WHEREAS, her remarkable achievement of "2026 Executive of the Year", awarded
by the Greater Baton Rouge Business Report, serves as a powerful testament to what
purposeful leadership, dedication, and vision can accomplish in service to others.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend and congratulate Renita Williams Thomas, MSN, RN, upon being
named the 2026 Executive of the Year by the Greater Baton Rouge Business Report and
does hereby recognize her extraordinary leadership, compassionate care, and steadfast
commitment to medically fragile children and their families.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
Renita Williams Thomas, MSN, RN.
